    "created_at": "2015-07-20T17:53:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-20T17:53:36Z",
    "body": "I explored the options of keeping the script outside the asar package as well as trying to use `fork` instead of `spawn`. \n\nKeeping it outside the package will not work as the spawning script itself uses a lot of \nother modules and keeping all of them outside of the package kind of beats the point of a package.\n\nAnd though fork seemed promising and did work in launching a child process, it seems to cause issues to Electron's Browser and/or Renderer processes - and a simple `mainWindow.loadUrl('http://localhost:3000/');` was not doing anything after using a fork.\n\nIs there a way I can use the internal/embedded node to spawn a child process, so that it will read the module within the asar package?\n"
  },
